4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT CREATING THE MONTANA BLOCKCHAIN AND DIGITAL
5 INNOVATION TASK FORCE; PROVIDING MEMBERSHIP REQUIREMENTS AND DUTIES; PROVIDING
6 REPORTING REQUIREMENTS; AND ; PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE; PROVIDING A
7 TERMINATION DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Montana blockchain and digital innovation task force -- membership
12 -- duties -- reporting. (1) There is a Montana blockchain and digital innovation task force administered by the
13 department of administration.
14 (2) The task force consists of:
15 (a) the attorney general or the attorney general's designee;
16 (b) the state auditor or the state auditor's designee;
17 (c) five members appointed by the president of the senate, including:
18 (i) one member of the senate;
19 (ii) two members who have experience in:
20 (A) blockchain;
21 (B) cryptocurrency;
22 (C) financial technology; or
23 (D) digital innovation technology; and
24 (iii) two additional members, one of whom is a representative of a business trade association;
25 (d) five members appointed by the speaker of the house, including:
26 (i) one member of the house of representatives;
27 (ii) two members who have experience in:
28 (A) blockchain;
